---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Banner from '../../components/Banner.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import { Banner } from 'comet-astro';

const action = { href: '/changelog', label: 'Learn more' };

---

<Banner
  title="Fresh capabilities just landed"
  description="We refreshed the monitoring dashboard and introduced a AAA-friendly night mode."
  action={action}
  variant="success"
  dismissible
/>`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Banner"
  description="High-impact announcement bar with AAA contrast, optional action, and reduced-motion dismiss animation."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      Drop a banner at the top of your page to call out critical updates. The
      component ships with four signal variants plus a neutral option, each
      tuned to hit AAA contrast in both themes. Layer in a call-to-action,
      replace the icon, pin it to the viewport, or offer a dismiss
      button—everything stays accessible out of the box.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      To maximize readability we lean on solid backgrounds instead of gradients.
      Text, buttons, and focus indicators remain crisp regardless of the
      colorway or theme.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          title?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Accessible heading for the banner. Short, direct phrases work best.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          description?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Optional body copy for added context. Omit it and flow content through
          the default slot instead.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          variant?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Visual treatment for the surface. Choose <code>default</code>, <code
            >success</code
          >, <code>warning</code>, or <code>danger</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          action?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Shape for the call-to-action button. Provide <code>label</code> and <code
            >href</code
          > to render a prominent link.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          dismissible?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Adds a close button that fades the banner out (or instantly removes it
          when motion is reduced). Disabled by default.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm sm:col-span-2"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          slot
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Drop in any extra markup between the description and action—lists,
          secondary links, or feature callouts.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Import the component, pass a title and description, and layer in an action
      or dismiss control when needed. Focus rings and contrast ratios are baked
      in, so you rarely need custom utility classes.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{usageSnippet}</code>
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Variants</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <Banner
        title="Maintenance window"
        description="Billing endpoints will be unavailable for up to 30 minutes on Sunday at 22:00."
        icon="🛠️"
        variant="default"
      />
      <Banner
        title="Migration complete"
        description="All workspaces now run on the new infrastructure with lower latency."
        icon="✅"
        action={{ href: '#', label: 'View status' }}
        variant="success"
      />
      <Banner
        title="Breaking change ahead"
        description="Legacy API v1 sunsets next week. Update your integrations before the cutoff."
        icon="⚠️"
        action={{ href: '#', label: 'Upgrade guide' }}
        variant="warning"
      />
      <Banner
        title="Email delays detected"
        description="Notification delivery is currently degraded. We’ll update once queues are healthy."
        icon="🚨"
        variant="danger"
        dismissible
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">
      Sticky &amp; Dismissible
    </h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Toggle <code>sticky</code> to pin the banner to the viewport. Combine it with
      <code>dismissible</code> and the component gracefully fades out (or simply
      disappears when reduced motion is preferred).
    </p>
    <Banner
      title="Live broadcast"
      description="System metrics remain visible in real time throughout the keynote."
      icon="📡"
      sticky
      dismissible
      action={{ href: '#', label: 'Join stream' }}
    />
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Every palette maintains at least a 9:1 contrast ratio between background
      and text. Actions get bold focus rings with color-aligned offsets so
      keyboard users can locate them instantly.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The element renders with <code>role="status"</code>, allowing assistive
      tech to announce changes without derailing the reading order. Localize
      titles and icons so all audiences receive the same signal.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
